"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The numpy.sinc function computes the normalized sinc function, which is defined as sin(pi*x)/(pi*x). For x=0, the result is 1, but for other values, the results are not necessarily 0. Therefore, the assertions for sinc_result[1] are incorrect.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7,8c7,8\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], np.sinc(1)), \\\"Results not close to expected value\\\"\\n\"\n}"